5	// Triggered by host opcode 0x30. Exercises each subsystem independently:
6	//   Test 0: BRAM write/read pattern (walking 1s)
7	//   Test 1: CIC impulse response check (known input → expected output)
8	//   Test 2: FFT known-input test (DC input → bin 0 peak)
9	//   Test 3: Arithmetic / saturating-add check
10	//   Test 4: ADC raw data capture (dump N samples to host)
11	//
12	// Results reported back via a status register readable by host (opcode 0x31).
13	// Each test produces a PASS/FAIL bit in result_flags[4:0].
14	//
15	// Integration: radar_system_top.v wires host_self_test_trigger (from opcode 0x30)
16	// to this module's `trigger` input, and reads `result_flags` / `result_valid`
17	// via opcode 0x31.
18	//
19	// Resource cost: ~200 LUTs, 1 BRAM (test pattern), 0 DSP.
